	   <tr><td colspan=2>I think you will decide that you want both.&nbsp;&nbsp;I have a level 39 human monk and a level 32 wood elf druid.  I play them both, and use their talents to benefit each other.  They are both in the same guild, and I have a character for almost every occasion.<br><br>That being said, I personally like the monk the best.  He can be soloed if necessary and makes a welcome addition to any group.  He travels relatively light and doesn't need much in the way of expensive weapons or armor.    <br><br>Really, I see no reason not to have both.  I test out new areas with my monk (the Feign Death skill is fantastic for getting out of tight spots), then I bring in the druid to take advantage of what I have learned.  If I find something No Drop that the monk can't use, I log on the druid to grab it up.<br><br>I can jump across the world in a hurry with the druid,  I can transport my friends or help someone in need and accept a nice tip with the druid.  I can forage my own food and usually enough for a few others, track my targets, buff my party, blast the target, heal everyone and evac them out if the going gets rough.<br><br>You choose, but you can have up to eight, so why stress.<br><br>Laredo, 39 Veeshan Monk <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
