	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9785467362458><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=9785467362458>RE: TO ANY GREAT MONKS</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=9785467362458#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=6833><span id= >Mordenkai</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>2 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jan 3rd 6:33 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>What you want to do is work up your 1hb, Hand 2 Hand, and your 2hb all at the same time.&nbsp;&nbsp;Start out maxing your best weapon, then move on to max out the other weapon types.   The reasoning behind maxing your best weapon first is, at the beginning of your new level, you will be fighting higher creatures, but your defence, and your offensive skills will be the same as last level. You will need to keep all your skills maxed. If you lag behind in one, it will be very impratical to work it up, and will hurt your soling/group at the time.  <br><br>For instance, you have you Hand 2 hand maxed out, and a friend gives you two trance sticks, unfortunatly you have not been keeping up with your 1hb, and you can barely hit anything with them. Now, because you can rarely do any kind of damage output, you will not be liked in a group, and soloing is definatly out.  So, you will have to waste time fighting stuff that you can hit (the creature you fight to get skill up must be able to give you experience from the kill or you cant get your offensive skills up) and not getting any or little experience.  <br><br>Why waste this time later on for something you could have kept up with in the beginning? If you figure out a reason, let me know.<br><br>Jang<br>14 Iksar Monk<br>Vallon Zek (8 lvl difference PvP teams server)<br>&nbsp;<br>Those who know most<br>speak least.</td></tr>
