	   <a name=97753439821290></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97753439821290><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=97753439821290>RE: Trade skills</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=97753439821290#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=7388><span id= >Novin</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>7 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Dec 23rd 1:20 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Yep, definatly tailoring... it's fairly profitable, you can sew your own armor, and sell armor to other monks, so your helping others of your own class by doing it. And the materials for tailoring... at least for silk armor... are very light... i can carry eight different stacks of patterns, containers to hold em in (recommend wrist pouches or bearskin potion bag), 2 stacks of heady kiola and as much silk as i can get my hands on for around 2 pounds... also its cool that you can do everything in the field. Make the kiola in town, then hunt up some spiders, get the silk, put up the "WTS Cured Silk", and you can sew it right on the spot. Also tailoring is VERY useful in the lower levels becuase it means you don't have to put any money towards leather seeing as you can make your own patchwork and raw silk armor. I started breaking even on cured silk around skill 45 or 50. Use swatches and patchwork to get you through the lower skill levels, then switch to raw silk, then cured. But if you do take up tailoring you will have to work on brewing. I don't know the best way to get this up becuase i got REALLY lucky, had a high level shammie pay me 180pps for a backpack full of Heady Kiolas. Started making that batch at skill 21, finished trivial for Kiola at 48, and made about 75pps off of it. Hope that helps :)<br><br>Novin<br>level 27, no wait now 26:(, monk<br>Quellious<br>Disposessed<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
