	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Dec 21st 12:49 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.14]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>To expand on the topic of Information Highway I would suggest that casters also need to be sending information to the tanks of the group.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>In my weekly group, the casters have used a similar method of programming hotkeys to tell the group what spell is being cast and at the same time what or who the spell is being cast.  So if a particular MOB is being mezzed, the lead tank knows to maybe pick a diffent MOB once the current target is dead.  Or if a MOB is being cast to death that the tanks know not to worry about targeting that particular creature.<br><br>I have found that the lack of information has been the reason for most of the deaths within our weekly group. It seems obvious, but the more you talk, the less likely you will be running through zones nude asking for SOW's.<br><br>Thunkum - Troll Warrior and parttime meat sheild.<br>Bristlebane<br><br>P.S.  If you are interested in the programming.../tell.  The group usually plays on Wednesday nite from 9pm - 11:00<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Shrikke - Knight of Fear<br>Bristlebane</td></tr>
